rent things. We like different things. It’s like they say with books, no two people ever read the same book. It’s the same with music, yo.\n\n- Fox Benwell, Kaleidoscope Song\n|\nAs an Odd-Fish, it is not my job to be right,' said Sir Oort. 'It is my job to be wrong in new and exciting ways.\n\n- James\n|\nWriting is a job, a talent, but it's also the place to go in your head. It is the imaginary friend you drink your tea with in the afternoon.\n\n- Ann Patchett, Truth and Beauty\n|\nHumanity takes itself too seriously. It is the world's original sin. If the cave-man had known how to laugh, History would have been different.\n\n- Oscar Wilde, The Picture of Dorian Gray\n|\nBooks aren't written - they're rewritten. Including your own. It is one of the hardest things to accept, especially after the seventh rewrite hasn't quite done it.\n\n- Michael\n|\nSome way some how i'm going to be happy i'm going to laugh i'm going to prosper,i feel good that i remain positive thru these mess up times!!!\n\n- jojo1980\n|\nHope is something that can never be taken from you unless you allow someone to take it. If you never lose hope, you will never truly be poor.\n\n- John M. Simmons, The Marvelous Journey Home\n|\nGoodness is, so to speak, itself: badness is only spoiled goodness.\n\n- C.S.\n|\nStudy to learn, do not study to pass'.\n\n- Kamaran Ihsan Salih, Latest Proverbs\n|\nThe fewer moving parts, the better.' 'Exactly. No truer words were ever spoken in the context of engineering.\n\n- Christian Cantrell, Containment\n|\nwhen you betray to someone , first you betray to yourself, who speak somewhere inside you that you are a good human\n\n- Mohammed Zaki Ansari, 'Zaki's Gift Of Love'\n|\nThere are ships sailing to many ports, but not a single one goes where life is not painful.\n\n- Fernando Pessoa, The Book of Disquiet\n|\nHope is the last thing that dies.Maybe because hope is one of those dratted things that is truly, honestly, genuinely immortal.\n\n- Vera Nazarian, The Perpetual Calendar of Inspiration\n|\nOne must not make too much of anything in life, good or bad.\n\n- Joseph Conrad, The Shadow-Line\n|\nIf I knew how a lot of my relationships would have turned out, I never would have gotten involved in them... And I would have missed out on some of the best times in my life.\n\n- L.A. Witt, Rules of Engagement\n|\nAnatasiaYou Are My More My Love, My LifeChristian\n\n- E.L. James, Fifty Shades Freed\n|\nThe glitter of the great world, you know, is only so much froth and spume: you may look in vain for happiness there.\n\n- Jude Morgan, Indiscretion\n|\nWhen you use your energy and resources to punish people, you run out of energy and resources to protect people.\n\n- Kelly Bryson, Don't Be Nice, Be Real: Balancing Passion for Self with Compassion for Others\n|\nMoney comes with a price, and for me, the price is both freedom and a real life.\n\n- Savi Sharma, Everyone Has A Story\n|\nToo often in my life, love has been defined as 'humiliation with occasional roses'.\n\n- Deb Caletti, The Secret Life of Prince Charming\n|\nIt goes with a courageous intent to greet the universe as it really is, not to foist our emotional predispositions on it but to courageously accept what our explorations tell us.\n\n- Carl Sagan, The Varieties of Scientific Experience: A Personal View of the Search for God\n|\nDespair is typical of those who do not understand the causes of evil, see no way out, and are incapable of struggle.\n\n- Vladimir\n|\nWE MUST ENJOY THE PRESENT, EVERYDAY THERE IS SOMETHING BEAUTIFUL AND AMAZING THAT WE CAN BE GRATEFUL FOR.\n\n- Linda Alfiori, The Art of Loving & The Peaceful Wristband: How to Keep The Atraction Alive and His Love Growing For You\n|\nTo see yourself and others in the darkness, be the light of courage and enlighten them.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nWe are beautiful because we are sons and daughters of God, not because we look a certain way.\n\n- Kate Wicker, Weightless: Making Peace with Your Body\n|\nThese things sneak 